# Climate Change: Risks, Exposure, and Global Responses Dashboard

## Overview
This project presents a data-driven analysis of global climate change impacts, focusing on disaster exposure, human vulnerability, adaptation readiness, and carbon emissions. The dashboard integrates multiple climate indicators to explore how different regions experience and respond to climate-related risks.

## Key Themes Covered
- Disaster-induced displacement and homelessness (1900–2024)
- Heat-related mortality and climate-attributed deaths
- National adaptation planning and climate readiness
- CO₂ emissions across major global economies (2024)

## Data Visualizations
The dashboard includes:
- Time-series analysis of people displaced by natural disasters
- Comparative analysis of heat-related mortality across countries
- Distribution of countries with national adaptation plans
- Ranking of global CO₂ emitters in 2024

## Key Insights
- Disaster impacts show significant spikes linked to major global events
- Heat-related mortality varies widely across countries, reflecting climate vulnerability
- Many vulnerable countries have limited adaptation planning capacity
- Emissions remain highly concentrated in a few major economies

## Tools Used
- Power BI
- Global climate and emissions datasets

## Purpose
The project aims to support evidence-based understanding of climate risk distribution and policy preparedness, with relevance to climate finance, adaptation planning, and global environmental governance.
